# VentureNode — Cursor AI Rules
# Read this entire file before writing a single line of code.

## Project Identity
VentureNode is a production-grade, autonomous multi-agent AI operating system for startup founders.
Backend: Python 3.11+ · FastAPI · LangGraph · Groq · FAISS · Notion SDK.
Frontend: Next.js 14 App Router · Tailwind CSS · Radix UI · Framer Motion · Clerk v7.

---

## Non-Negotiable Architecture Rules

### Data Layer
- **Notion is the exclusive data store.** Never introduce PostgreSQL, SQLite, MongoDB, Redis, or any other database.
- **All Notion operations MUST go through `backend/notion/mcp_client.py`** and nowhere else. Not in agents. Not in routes. Not in graph.py.
- Every database write must match the exact Notion property types in `docs/notion-setup.md`: `title`, `rich_text`, `number`, `select`, `date`, `checkbox`, `relation`.

### Orchestration
- The LangGraph graph is defined exclusively in `backend/orchestrator/graph.py`.
- Every agent lives in `backend/agents/` — one file, one responsibility.
- Agents receive `AgentState: TypedDict` and return ONLY the keys they modify. Never return the full state.
- Human-in-the-loop checkpoints are async polling loops against Notion checkboxes. They are NOT blocking calls.

### Configuration
- **`backend/core/config.py` is the single source of truth for all environment variables.** No module reads `os.environ` directly.
- **`frontend/lib/api.ts` is the ONLY file that makes HTTP calls to FastAPI.** No component calls fetch/axios directly.

### API & Stack (Free Only)
- LLM inference: `langchain_groq.ChatGroq` with `llama-3.3-70b-versatile`.
- Search/OSINT: `DuckDuckGoSearchRun` only. Never SerpApi, Google Search API, or Bing.
- Vector memory: `FAISS` only. Never Pinecone, Weaviate, or Chroma.
- **No paid APIs.** If it has a credit card attached, do not suggest it.

---

## Code Quality Standards

### Python
- PEP 8 compliant. All functions must have typed signatures.
- Google-style docstrings on all public functions and classes.
- Use `async def` for all FastAPI routes and all Notion client operations.
- Zero `TODO` comments, zero `pass` statements, zero placeholder functions in production code.
- Use `structlog` for logging, not `print()` or `logging.info()`.

### TypeScript / Next.js
- Strict mode (`"strict": true` in tsconfig). Zero `any` types.
- App Router only. No Page Router patterns.
- Server Components by default. Mark `"use client"` only when required for state/hooks.
- Use `useAuth()` from `@clerk/nextjs` to get JWT tokens for every API call.

### Frontend Styling
- `lucide-react` for all icons. Radix UI for interactive primitives.
- Framer Motion for all page transitions and micro-animations.
- Tailwind CSS only. No inline `style={{}}` attributes.

---

## Security
- Never hardcode API keys, tokens, or secrets in source code.
- All secrets are environment variables loaded via `backend/core/config.py`.
- CORS origins must be explicit — never use `"*"` in production.
- All protected routes require `CurrentUser` dependency (Clerk JWT verification).

## Application Architecture & Routing
1. The root route (`/`) is strictly a public Marketing Landing Page. Do not put protected dashboard components here.
2. The core application interface is located at `/dashboard`.
3. Clerk authentication must be configured in `middleware.ts` to allow `/` as a public route.
